<html xmlns:py="http://genshi.edgewall.org/" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" py:strip="">


<py:def function="announcement_id">
PMASA-2005-3
</py:def>

<py:def function="announcement_date">
2005-04-03
</py:def>

<py:def function="announcement_summary">
Cross-Site Scripting vulnerability
</py:def>


<py:def function="announcement_description">
We received a security advisory from Oriol Torrent Santiago and we wish to thank him for his work and report. The <tt>convcharset</tt> parameter was not correctly validated, opening the door to a XSS attack.
</py:def>


<py:def function="announcement_severity">
We consider this vulnerability to be serious.

</py:def>


<py:def function="announcement_affected">
Probably all phpMyAdmin versions before 2.6.2-rc1.
</py:def>


<py:def function="announcement_solution">
Upgrade to phpMyAdmin 2.6.2-rc1 or newer.
</py:def>


<py:def function="announcement_references">
<a href="http://www.arrelnet.com/advisories/adv20050403.html">
http://www.arrelnet.com/advisories/adv20050403.html</a>
</py:def>

<py:def function="announcement_cve">
CVE-2005-0992
</py:def>

